history.content: Your summer instructors will help you sign-up once they have the information. Undergraduates cannot enroll in CS or EE 375 directly either way. (And if you've already taken CS 370 in an eligible semester, they'll likely recommend that you do not enroll at all in CS 375.)

Your summer instructors will help you sign-up once they have the information. Undergraduates cannot enroll in 300-level courses directly either way. (And if you've already taken CS 370 in an eligible semester, they'll likely recommend that you do not enroll at all in CS 375.)

Where can I get information about how to enroll in CS 375 over the summer? I will be a first-time TA in the summer; I have taken 370 and am afraid that I will be skipped for enrollment in 375 because of this.
history.subject: CS 375 Summer Enrollment
